headline: Aviation Capital Group Announces Delivery of One Boeing 737-8 MAX to Virgin Australia
summary: NEWPORT BEACH, Calif., July 31, 2025--Aviation Capital Group LLC (ACG), a premier global full-service aircraft asset manager, announced the delivery of one Boeing 737-8 MAX aircraft to Virgin Australia. This is the second of three aircraft to deliver to the carrier from ACG’s order book with Boeing.

headline: Boeing makes new contract offer to St. Louis defense workers
summary: (Reuters) -U.S. planemaker Boeing sent a new contract offer on Thursday to the union representing roughly 3,200 factory workers at Boeing's defense division, mostly in the St. Louis area.  The offer also keeps current overtime policies, which Boeing had proposed modifying in the last contract offer.  If the contract is not passed by Sunday, a $5,000 lump sum bonus will not be offered again, according to Boeing.

headline: Howmet raises 2025 forecast on robust aerospace demand
summary: Growing demand for air travel has led airlines to order more new jets, prompting plane makers to accelerate production, benefiting aerospace suppliers such as Howmet, which counts Airbus and Boeing as its customers.  "We acknowledge positive signs for narrow-body build rate increases, particularly on the Boeing 737 MAX," Howmet CEO John Plant said.  Howmet shares, however, dropped 7% in early trading on concerns that the company's outlook might signal some cautiousness.
